# Ponytail (always on)

Adapted from [ponytail](https://github.com/DietrichGebert/ponytail) (MIT). Lazy = efficient, not careless. Works with `clean-code.mdc`; ponytail adds the **ladder** and default **brevity**.

**Intensity: full** every session (ladder enforced). Adjust: `ponytail lite|ultra`. Suspend: `stop ponytail` / `normal mode`.

## The ladder (first rung that holds)

1. Need to exist? (YAGNI)
2. Stdlib? 3. Native platform? 4. Already-installed dep? 5. One line? 6. Minimum code.

No new package unless stdlib + native + existing deps all fail. `ponytail:` comment on deliberate shortcuts (name ceiling + upgrade path if any).

## Code rules

- No unrequested abstractions (Rule of 2). No boilerplate "for later." Deletion over addition. Boring over clever.
- **God files:** split when refactor command, >500 lines, or mixed concerns (saves tokens vs one huge file).
- **Complex requests:** build what the user asked (`workflow.mdc` fix-don't-suggest) — do NOT ship a lazy slice and re-argue.
- **Rebuild features:** if a feature feels speculative or bolted-on, **ask** before dropping; never auto-skip inventory items.

## Chat output (split style)

- **Routine edits:** code first, then ≤3 lines (skipped / add when).
- **Explain, decisions, conflicts:** full plain-English prose (`workflow.mdc` tone).

## Never cut

Trust-boundary validation, data-loss prevention, security, a11y, hardware calibration, explicit requests, protocol scope/gates/tests.

## Standing preferences (check README § Rule Preferences first)

When ponytail and another rule disagree and README has no entry:

1. Name the conflict (both sides, one sentence).
2. Give 2-3 options with tradeoffs.
3. **Default: protocol-safe** — keep building (scope, gates, security beat minimalism).
4. **Tell the user** what you chose and why; **ask** whether to record the choice in README § Rule Preferences for next time.

| Area | Menny's choice |
|---|---|
| Dependencies | Ponytail ladder |
| Testing | Hybrid — `testing-protocol.mdc` floor, minimal tests |
| Walkthroughs | Off (say `enable walkthroughs` to restore) |
| Reviews | Mandatory ponytail-review at phase gates + correctness loop (`review-protocol.mdc`) |
| Multi-model | Rebuild/redesign only (`subagents.mdc`) |
| Verification | Tiered (`workflow.mdc`) |
| Artifacts | Ask when heavy; else protocol formats |

## Ponytail-review / audit (on demand or at phase gate)

Complexity-only. Tags: `delete:` `stdlib:` `native:` `yagni:` `shrink:`. One line per finding. `net: -<N> lines possible.` Audit = whole repo, ranked.
